Steps to create AWS EC2 Instance
1. Prerequisites for Linux Team with Admin Access
Install Required Packages
Switch to root user: sudo su
Run the commands:
sudo su

yum install net-tools
yum install ntpstat
yum install wget

Set Hostname
Use the command:
hostnamectl set-hostname <COMPONENT_NAME>

Create Splunk User and Directory
Run the following commands:
useradd splunk
groupadd splunk
mkdir /opt/splunk
chown -R splunk:splunk /opt/splunk

Disable Transparent Huge Pages (THP)
Steps to Disable THP:
Switch to root user and go to /etc/init.d/ directory:
cd /etc/init.d/

Create a script to disable THP:
vi disable_thp

Paste the following code in the file:
#!/bin/bash
### BEGIN INIT INFO
# Provides:          disable-thp
# Required-Start:    $local_fs
# Default-Start:     2 3 4 5
### END INIT INFO

case $1 in
 start)
   if [ -d /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage ]; then
     thp_path=/sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage
   elif [ -d /sys/kernel/mm/redhat_transparent_hugepage ]; then
     thp_path=/sys/kernel/mm/redhat_transparent_hugepage
   else
     return 0
   fi

   echo 'never' > ${thp_path}/enabled
   echo 'never' > ${thp_path}/defrag

   if [[ $(cat ${thp_path}/khugepaged/defrag) =~ ^[0-1]+$ ]]; then
     echo 0  > ${thp_path}/khugepaged/defrag
   else
     echo 'no' > ${thp_path}/khugepaged/defrag
   fi
   ;;
esac

Save the file: Press Esc, type :wq!
Verify the file content:
cat disable_thp

Add execute permission to the file:
chmod 755 disable_thp

Add the script to system startup:
sudo chkconfig --add disable_thp

Increase ulimit
Open the limits.conf file:
vi /etc/security/limits.conf

Add the following lines at the end of the file:
* soft nofile 64000
* hard nofile unlimited
* soft nproc 16000
* hard nproc unlimited
* soft data 8000000
* hard data unlimited
* soft fsize unlimited
* hard fsize unlimited

Save the file: Press Esc, type :wq!
Reboot the server:
reboot

Check the ulimit values:
ulimit -a splunk

or
sudo cat /etc/security/limits.conf

Verify THP is Disabled
Run the commands:
sudo cat /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/enabled
sudo cat /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/defrag

Look for [never] in the output.
After Splunk Installation,
Enable Bootstart for Splunk
Switch to root user:
sudo su

Enable Splunk boot start:
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start -user splunk

